    xQTLdownload_eqtlSig

    xQTLdownload_eqtlSig.Rd

    download significant eQTL associations of a tissue or across all tissues.

    Usage

    xQTLdownload_eqtlSig(
  variantName = "",
  genes = "",
  variantType = "auto",
  geneType = "auto",
  tissueSiteDetail = "",
  datasetId = "gtex_v8"
)

    Arguments

    variantName

    A character string. like dbsnp ID or variant id in GTEx.

    genes

    A gene symbol or a gencode id (versioned).

    variantType

    A character string. "auto", "snpId" or "variantId". Default: "auto".

    geneType

    A character string. "auto","geneSymbol" or "gencodeId". Default: "auto".

    tissueSiteDetail

    A character string. tissue detail can be listed using \"tissueSiteDetailGTExv8\" or \"tissueSiteDetailGTExv7\"

    datasetId

    A character string. "gtex_v8" or "gtex_v7". Default: "gtex_v8".

    Value

    A data.table

    Examples

    # \donttest{
 # Download eQTL info for a variant:
 xQTLdownload_eqtlSig("rs201327123")
